Interface Printer

public interface Printer
Printer is a singleton system component that prints collections of datamodel objects into a StringBuilder in a table-format.
Version:
"1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-E12_REFACTORING"
Author:
"sgra64"

    • printStreamed

      <T> StringBuilder printStreamed(Iterable<T> collection, Function<Stream<T>,Stream<T>> callout)

      Generic print method for a list of objects of datamodel classes of type <T> in table format into a StringBuilder.

      T can be any of class: Customer, Article or Order.

      Method will invoke the underlying print-methods for these classes.

      Before, the list of objects is converted to a Stream<T> passed back to the caller allowing to rearrange the Stream<T> for printing.

      Print orders in table format into a StringBuilder. Parameter streamCallout passes the stream of orders to caller to perform stream-operation such as filter(), sort(), or limit().
      Type Parameters:
      T - generic type of datamodel classes, can be: Customer, Article or Order.
      Parameters:
      collection - collection of objects of type <T> to print.
      callout - function for the caller to manipulate the stream before printing.
      Returns:
      StringBuilder with printed objects rendered as table.
